<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Apple-Glazed Roast Pork</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Try it</cat>
        <cat>Pork</cat>
        <cat>Crockpot</cat></categories>
      <yield>8</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing-div>
        <title>RIVAL CROCK-POT COOKING</title>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>4</qty>
            <unit>pounds</unit></amt>
          <item>Pork loin roast</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>6</qty>
            <unit/></amt>
          <item>Apples</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/4</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Apple juice</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>3</qty>
            <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
          <item>Sugar, brown</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
          <item>Ginger, ground</item></ing></ing-div></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Rub roast with salt and pepper.  Brown pork roast under broiler to remove
  excess fat; drain well.
  
  Core and quarter apples.  Place apple quarters in bottom of crockpot. Place
  roast on top of apples.  Combine apple juice, brown sugar, and ginger.
  Spoon over top surface of roast, moistening well. Cover and cook on Low
  10-12 hours, until done.
  
  File ftp://ftp.idiscover.co.uk/pub/food/mealmaster/recipes/mmdjaxxx.zip
 
</step></directions></recipe></recipeml>
